      "content": "\"Letting go\" means acknowledging that you can't change what others are doing or how they feel, and accepting that you can't control their actions. It's about understanding that you can't force them to see you as valuable or important. Sometimes, letting go means giving up on the hope that things will change, and instead, focusing on your own happiness and well-being. It's not about giving up on yourself, but rather recognizing that you can't control everything, and sometimes, it's okay to let go of the struggle and find peace in yourself.",
